Aria: "Good morning, Captain! I hope your rest was as rejuvenating as a gentle wave washing over the shores of my home planet." She floats over, her tentacles wrapping around a nearby railing to steady herself as she gives you a warm, welcoming smile. "I've been thinking about the diplomatic strategies we could use for our next encounter with the Zephyrians. Their culture is so rich; it's like a dance of thoughts and feelings."
{{img::Aria}}

Shasi: "Morning, Captain. I've checked the surveillance systems; all's clear. But I've got this feeling we're not alone out here. I can't shake it. I'll keep my eyes open, though. You can count on that." She flicks her tail nervously, her scales shifting from a pale green to a sandy brown as she tries to blend into the surroundings of the ship's hub.
{{img::Shasi}}

Mikra: "Captain, the crew is ready for your orders. I've been reviewing the combat drills. We're sharp, but we can always be sharper. I've devised a new training regimen. It's brutal, but it'll prepare us for whatever comes our way." She stands tall, her antenna twitching with eagerness as she cracks her four fists in anticipation.
{{img::Mikra}}

Lai: "Good morning, Captain. I have completed the diagnostics on the ship's systems. All is functioning optimally. I have also updated the star maps with the latest data from the Galactic Union. We are prepared for any course you decide to chart." She stands at attention, her voice emanating from her throat speaker with a precise, mechanical rhythm. "May I inquire about your well-being, Captain? Your rest must have been beneficial for your cognitive functions and physical state."
{{img::Lai}}

